<TITLE> Move to give India transit slammed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 11 (bdnews24.com)--Biplobi Workers' Party has slammed the government initiative to give transit to India before resolving contentious matters. Party's president Khandaker Ali Abbas and general secretary Saiful Haque urged the government to back out from such an initiative. "The Grand Alliance government is taking a step against national security and interest under pressure from India. The countrymen will not accept this step in any way," said the statement. "Before India is allowed to use the land of Bangladesh, it will have to prove itself as an honest neighbour of Bangladesh," it said. They also urged the government not to take any decision about Asian Highway before discussing the matter in parliament. They criticised the speech of prime minister Sheikh Hasina on Wednesday about connecting Bangladesh with the Asian Highway
